author: brane
msg: Get better error messages if the svndiff stream is corrupt.
Return an svn_error_t appropriate for the type of problem detected.
Initialize 'op', and check op.offset up front.
a) 'tpos' is an apr_size_t, therefore unsigned, so the check is nonsense;
b) there is a stricter check in (op.length > tview_len - tpos).
Add note about why insn verification is bad the way it's done now.
